{
  "texts": [
    "Similar to query languages like SQL or SPARQL, QDMR uses a sequence of operations to select entities, retrieve information, and aggregate results.",
    "QDMR has been shown to improve question answering tasks and simplify complex logical forms used in semantic parsing.",
    "In contrast to previous frameworks, QDMR focuses on explaining natural language questions, while ETT focuses on explaining programming languages.",
    "We transform natural language questions into their https://api.python.langchain.com/en/latest/example_selectors/ langchain_core.example_selectors.semantic_similarity.",
    "SemanticSimilarityExampleSelector.html QDMR using the method and model outlined in Wolfson et al. (2020)."
  ]
}